One person died and eleven others injured after a taxi driver lost control of his vehicle on the R29 towards High Flats in KwaZulu Natal on Saturday.On arrical paramedics found the roof of the taxi had been removed by the fire department to save the driver and passengers.ER24 Spokesperson Annine Dormehl said most of the patients were transported to GJ Crookes Hospital in Scottburgh in KwaZulu Natal. Three of the patients were in a critical condition, while nine others sustained moderate injuries. One patient was declared dead.Local authorities are investigating the accident.-TNA Reporter